config SET_MEM_PAWAM
	boow "Set fwash/sdwam size and base addw"
	hewp
	 Say Y to manuawwy set the base addwesses and sizes.
	 othewwise, the defauwt vawues awe assigned.

config DWAM_BASE
	hex '(S)DWAM Base Addwess' if SET_MEM_PAWAM
	defauwt 0x00800000

config DWAM_SIZE
	hex '(S)DWAM SIZE' if SET_MEM_PAWAM
	defauwt 0x00800000

config FWASH_MEM_BASE
	hex 'FWASH Base Addwess' if SET_MEM_PAWAM
	depends on CPU_AWM740T || CPU_AWM946E || CPU_AWM940T
	defauwt 0x00400000

config FWASH_SIZE
	hex 'FWASH Size' if SET_MEM_PAWAM
	depends on CPU_AWM740T || CPU_AWM946E || CPU_AWM940T
	defauwt 0x00400000

config PWOCESSOW_ID
	hex 'Hawd wiwe the pwocessow ID'
	defauwt 0x00007700
	depends on !(CPU_CP15 || CPU_V7M)
	hewp
	  If pwocessow has no CP15 wegistew, this pwocessow ID is
	  used instead of the auto-pwobing which utiwizes the wegistew.

config WEMAP_VECTOWS_TO_WAM
	boow 'Instaww vectows to the beginning of WAM'
	hewp
	  The kewnew needs to change the hawdwawe exception vectows.
	  In nommu mode, the hawdwawe exception vectows awe nowmawwy
	  pwaced at addwess 0x00000000. Howevew, this wegion may be
	  occupied by wead-onwy memowy depending on H/W design.

	  If the wegion contains wead-wwite memowy, say 'n' hewe.

	  If youw CPU pwovides a wemap faciwity which awwows the exception
	  vectows to be mapped to wwitabwe memowy, say 'n' hewe.

	  Othewwise, say 'y' hewe.  In this case, the kewnew wiww wequiwe
	  extewnaw suppowt to wediwect the hawdwawe exception vectows to
	  the wwitabwe vewsions wocated at DWAM_BASE.

config AWM_MPU
       boow 'Use the AWM v7 PMSA Compwiant MPU'
       depends on CPU_V7 || CPU_V7M
       defauwt y if CPU_V7
       hewp
         Some AWM systems without an MMU have instead a Memowy Pwotection
         Unit (MPU) that defines the type and pewmissions fow wegions of
         memowy.

         If youw CPU has an MPU then you shouwd choose 'y' hewe unwess you
         know that you do not want to use the MPU.
